description: Deep Red. Very large, semidouble. Vigorous, upright growth. M. (Reticulata "Tali Queen' seedling). (Aus. 1970 - Sebire).

name: Burgundy Rose
description: Burgundy. Medium, anemone form. Average, upright growth. M-L. (U.S. 2015 - Gordy).

name: Burma Baby
description: White washed and veined Pink. Small, single. Vigorous, open growth. E. (Japonica × Irrawadiensis). (U.S. 1965 - Hilsman).

name: Burma Beatnik
description: Red. Medium, anemone form. Vigorous, open growth. E-M. (Japonica × Irrawadiensis). (U.S. 1965 - Hilsman).

name: Burneyville
description: Light Rose Pink. Medium, anemone form. Upright, compact growth. M-L. (U.S. 1951 - Riverbank).

name: Burnham Beeches
description: Pink edged White. Large, peony form. (Sport of Japonica 'Countess of Orkney'). (Aus. 1952 - Waterhouse).

name: Burtiane
description: Light Pink. Medium, single. Vigorous, compact, upright growth. M. (Aus. 1968 - I. D. Burt, Killara, NSW).

name: Busch Garden Red
description: See 'Rose Queen'.

name: Buster Bush
description: Pink veined Dark Pink to Light Red. Very large, semidouble to loose peony form. Average, upright, open growth. M. (Reticulata hybrid 'Buddha' x Reticulata hybrid 'Trewithin Pink'). (U.S. 1990 - Homeyer).

name: Buster Lewis
description: Deep Pink. Very large, semidouble. Average growth. M. (U.S. 1965 - C. E. Morgan, Greenville, SC).

name: Buster Newman
description: Deep Red. Medium to large, loose peony form with folded petals. Average, upright growth. M. (U.S. 1957 - Beasley).

name: Butch Burton
description: Light Pink with Yellow anthers and White filaments. Large, semidouble to loose peony form. Average, upright, open growth. E-L. (U.S. 2018 - Pat B. Johnson, Cairo, GA).

name: Butchie
description: Rose Pink. Very large, anemone to peony form. Average, spreding, upright growth. M-L. (U.S. 1999 - W. T. Shepherd, N. Charleston, SC).

description: Pink to Lavender Pink, darker at edges. Miniature to small, semidouble to rose form double. Vigorous, upright growth. (U.S. 2003 - Robert W. Butler, Hilton Head Island, SC).

name: Butterfly Girl
description: Pale Pink, fading to Lighter Pink at center. Very large, semidouble to peony form. Vigorous, upright growth. M. (Reticulata hybrid 'Suzanne Withers' x Reticulata hybrid 'Jean Pursel'). (Aus. 2000 - Dr. R. M. Withers, Donvale, Vic.)

name: Butterfly Pink
description: ('Fenhudie' - Chinese Name). Veined Pink. Medium to large, semidouble with irregular, wavy petals. M. (Yunnan Reticulata). (China to U.S. 1980 - U. C. Bot. Gdn, CA).

name: Butterfly Spring
description: ('Fu Dei Qiuan' - Chinese Name). Medium Pink. Large, formal double with inner petals incurved and outer petals well-branched growth. (Reticulata hybrid Suzanne Withers x Japonica). Vigorous, upright growth.

name: Buttermint
description: Very Creamy White to Pale Yellow. Miniature, formal double to rose form double to occasionally peony form. Average, upright growth. E-L. (Kissi seedling). (U.S. 1997 - Nuccio's).

name: Buttons 'n Bows
description: Light Pink shading deeper at edge. Small, formal double. Average, compact growth. E-M. (Saluenensis hybrid). (U.S. 1985 - Nuccio's).

name: Buzz Aldrin
description: Light Pink. Large, anemone form. Average growth. E. (Japonica 'Reg Ragland' × Granthamiana). (U.S. 1971 - Dr. R. K. Womack, Shreveport, LA).
